fields.Title: BOARDWALK / TRANT HEIDELSTAM INTRO
fields.Description:
Trant Heidelstam is chilling near the FELD building, with kid, piggy-bank. You can:
1. Learn about the FELD building.
2. Get useless advice.

fields.Dialogue Text: "And, as you know, they have this very distinctive dress uniform with scarlet breeches and little cylindrical fur caps, I think these are called..." You daze off, as Trant tells you about the peculiarities of mounted police forces in central Occident.

fields.Title: You: ""I want to hear about the Feld buil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I want to hear about the Feld building again..."

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""How to climb that ladder, you say?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How to climb that ladder, you say?" He turns around, eyeing the bleak metal bars next to the giant mural. "I do know that the Lomanthangs used *sticks* to climb battlements, there's even a special technique for that."

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""No, thanks to *you* for having me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, thanks to *you* for having me and little Mikael here to pick your brain... A very interesting conversation indeed."

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""I'm just spending time with my kid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just spending time with my kid here, showing him around the lesser-known parts of our home town... It wouldn't be *wise* to carry huge amounts of cash on such expeditions!"

fields.Dialogue Text: Hold on, what's R&D?

fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, this is just the sort of reasonable authority you're looking for!

fields.Title: You: ""So how does one go about contactin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So how does one go about contacting a Coalition warship?" (Proceed.)

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""Ah, well, it is one of the most he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, well, it is one of the most heavily armed aerostatics to ever fly. I've heard it said that the Archer is capable of engaging whole fleets of lesser vessels *from multiple sides* simultaneously. How about that?"

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""I believe that is intentional. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I believe that is intentional. You see, the Coalition are very sensitive to how they are perceived by the people of Revachol, which is why they generally prefer for their warships to remain at a discreet distance from major population centres..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmmm, no one would mistake them fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmmm, no one would mistake them for Feld engineers, but perhaps your young friends in the *tent* might be of assistance?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "You *will* figure it out. Something..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You *will* figure it out. Something tells you the person you're looking for is already on this coast...

fields.Dialogue Text: "A-ha, but it's not just *any* empty old building!" He raises his hand to his eyes to shield himself from the pattering rain. All four of you turn to admire the mural before you.

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""Then I guess everything got said,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then I guess everything got said, right?" He looks up to the sky. "The drizzle... it never seems to stop, does it?"

fields.Title: Mikael Heidelstam: ""The Revolution?" The boy wipes his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Revolution?" The boy wipes his nose on his sleeve.

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""Unfortunately their moonshot proje..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Unfortunately their moonshot project never made it to the market." He nods. "Feld's move to Revachol backfired. The Revolutionary government liquefied their assets and expropriated those very advanced prototypes. Possibly from this very building... or one of the adjacent ruins." He pauses, pointing to the other building, then continues:

fields.Title: Shivers: "Two seagulls circle in the sky. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Two seagulls circle in the sky. You look up and think: really? Or was there a fourth prototype that remains hidden in the mausoleums below Coal City?...

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""Oh, no, I don't have it *on me*, o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, no, I don't have it *on me*, officer, I was talking in more... general terms." He looks uncomfortable, his left hand squeezing his son's shoulder.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not really interested in the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not really interested in the practice, I just want to know how often you work out. Now and then -- that's what, like once a week?"

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""But anyway," he says after a while..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But anyway," he says after a while with a charming, apologetic smile, "I am boring you with details again. You were saying?"

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""If I'm not mistaken then it involv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If I'm not mistaken then it involved months of following a very rigid exercise regimen. No, *years*..."

fields.Title: Trant Heidelstam: ""Yes, they even built a pleasure wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, they even built a pleasure wheel, but that got destroyed in the war."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Wow, get a load of this guy. He *re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow, get a load of this guy. He *really* enjoys his trivia. The Orbis programming language was named after its inventor, Viktor Orbis, a cybernetician from Graad. They run Vox in the Occidental countries...
